            . On the evening of the 1st of February I was in High-street, St. Giles', and saw the prisoner, in company with another person - I followed the prisoner, who was going my way; I met Betraun - we followed the prisoner and the other on to Holborn, and from there on to <placeName id="t18310217-217-crimeloc1271">Great Warner-street, Clerkenwell</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310217-217-crimeloc1271" type="placeName" value="Great Warner-street, Clerkenwell"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310217-217-crimeloc1271" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-217-off1268 t18310217-217-crimeloc1271"></join>; I there saw his companion push open the door of the shop No. 9 - he came out again immediately, and joined the prisoner, who was close by him when he went in - they then both ran off. I followed them, and laid hold of both of them; but the other got away; I kept the prisoner till Betraun came up.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-217-person2037">
